{"id":3603,"date":"2018-05-19T07:11:53","date_gmt":"2018-05-19T07:11:53","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/?p=3603"},"modified":"2018-05-19T07:56:39","modified_gmt":"2018-05-19T07:56:39","slug":"tracking-sent-emails","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/tracking-sent-emails\/","title":{"rendered":"Tracking Sent Emails"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>From version 2.0 there is a new unique feature added in Perfex CRM for tracking sent emails if they are opened for the &#8220;sales&#8221; features. This feature will help you to easily determine eq if contact opened the email when you send the invoice to the contact email.<\/p>\n<p>This is only applied to specific emails, below you can find the list which emails\/email templates are tracked.<\/p>\n<ol>\n<li>Send Invoice to Customer<\/li>\n<li>Invoice Already Sent to Customer<\/li>\n<li>Invoice Overdue Notice<\/li>\n<li>Send Estimate to Customer<\/li>\n<li>Estimate Already Sent to Customer<\/li>\n<li>Estimate Expiration Reminder<\/li>\n<li>Send Proposal to Customer<\/li>\n<li>New Comment (Sent to Customer\/Lead)<\/li>\n<li>Proposal Expiration Reminder<\/li>\n<li>Send Credit Note To Email<\/li>\n<li>Send Contract to Customer<\/li>\n<li>Send Subscription to Customer<\/li>\n<li>Subscription Payment Failed<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<p>You can check all available email template mentioned above in <strong>Setup-&gt;Email Templates<\/strong>.<\/p>\n<hr \/>\n<h3>Checking if the email is opened<\/h3>\n<p>You don&#8217;t need to configure anything, the feature is auto turned ON and will work out of the box while you use Perfex CRM.<\/p>\n<p>Let&#8217;s assume you\u00a0sent\u00a0an invoice to a contact and you want to see if the contact opened the email, in admin area open the invoice preview area and click on the envelope\u00a0menu icon, there will be a list of all tracked emails sent with indicator does they are opened or not.<\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-3604\" src=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/05\/perfex-crm-sent-emails-tracking.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"971\" height=\"357\" srcset=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/05\/perfex-crm-sent-emails-tracking.png 971w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/05\/perfex-crm-sent-emails-tracking-300x110.png 300w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/05\/perfex-crm-sent-emails-tracking-768x282.png 768w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/05\/perfex-crm-sent-emails-tracking-60x22.png 60w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/05\/perfex-crm-sent-emails-tracking-150x55.png 150w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 971px) 100vw, 971px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Use same steps to see if the email is opened is applied for all other features.<\/p>\n<h3>Tracked emails not updated<\/h3>\n<p>There is one occasion when this feature may not work properly, depends on the settings the contact\/user configure in his email client. There is nothing Perfex CRM can do about this, the tracked email status will remain as <b>&#8220;<strong>Not Opened<\/strong>&#8220;<\/b><\/p>\n<p>If the contact\/user have an option\u00a0in his email client\/email interface to <strong>turn off remote content for the received emails, this may not work properly<\/strong>. Below you can find an example how this may look eq in <strong>Thunderbird<\/strong> email client<\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-3605\" src=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/05\/emails-tracking-privacy-1024x80.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"980\" height=\"77\" srcset=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/05\/emails-tracking-privacy-1024x80.png 1024w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/05\/emails-tracking-privacy-300x24.png 300w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/05\/emails-tracking-privacy-768x60.png 768w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/05\/emails-tracking-privacy-60x5.png 60w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/05\/emails-tracking-privacy-150x12.png 150w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/05\/emails-tracking-privacy.png 1311w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 980px) 100vw, 980px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>In this case, if contact just read the email and don&#8217;t turn on remote content or don&#8217;t allow remote content for this specific email, the email will remain as &#8220;<strong>Not Opened<\/strong>&#8221;<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>From version 2.0 there is a new unique feature added in Perfex CRM for tracking sent emails if they are opened for the &#8220;sales&#8221; features. This feature will help you to easily determine eq if contact opened the email when you send the invoice to the contact email. This is only applied to specific emails, [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[20],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-3603","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","hentry","category-general"],"aioseo_notices":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/3603","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=3603"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/3603\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp